example video:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sav98y4EFzE&list=PLJG25HlmvsOWvVjF44qr5-xXG--cCuXnn&index=24&t=0s

example text:
https://github.com/nikku/camunda-modeler-plugins-talk-2019

plugin folder:
Linux:
cd $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/camunda-modeler/resources/plugins 
or
cd ~/.config/camunda-modeler/resources/plugins

MacOS:
cd ~/Library/Application\ Support/camunda-modeler/resources/plugins

install plugin:
just git clone the repo in the plugin folder.
In the example text, it uses npx + npm install. I am not sure if it is necessary only when we need to develop a plugin.
git clone github:bpmn-io/bpmn-js-token-simulation-plugin
git clone github:camunda/camunda-modeler-linter-plugin
git clone git@github.com:umb/camunda-modeler-property-info-plugin.git



workshop
install plugin in plugin folder:
npx degit github:camunda/camunda-modeler-linter-plugin camunda-modeler-linter-plugin



enable plugin:
modeler > plugins
